communityItemData.itemDescription: "Well anyhow, Here we are! I just got back from the concert, It was fabulous!"
"I am very proud of my country and my tradition... You need to have values that light your path in hard times..."
"Hey, watch out! That tickles!"
"Ok, so you think you are so smart, right? That's not how you speak, to girls you know. You should just be more approachable..."
"Ha! You are sweet.  Almost as sweet as a dried pumpkin. It's foxes' favorite food, you know... well apart from what we hunt down, but we'll talk about that later. Ha Ha!"
"It's nice you could make it! We were looking forward to meeting you!"
Well, we're bored. Come on think of something to do! We are gonna go to the bathroom and fix our makeup and in the meantime, think!
"What are we going to do at this hour? It's late.  Well ok! Maybe we can stay together just a bit more..."
"Ah yeah, dancing and making some noise while doing it! This is what cat girls love the most!"
"Yes! Comfortable clothes! Woohoo! How do you like that outfit, is it good? No... don't say a thing, I know it's good!"
"It's good to finally meet you in person! Do you feel the air after the rain? That's the best smell ever!"
"You are Nice! Nice and sweet...  And I don't think you are our type of guy, to be honest..."
"Well, you haven't been around for a while. What gives mister?"
"But... Why are you are not sure if you like us?"
"Ha Ha, don't look at us like that!"
"A nice break from boring office work!"
"I just wish, we have all met together earlier!"
"Well. We are sure you will learn to keep clean some day"
"We could use something cold to drink"
"Had a good night sleep?"
"We have spent so much quality time together..."

A sprawling library is illuminated by the pale moon. 
A longing melancholy pricks at your undead heart but passes just as quickly, as you turn your eyes to the books. Yes, all the knowledge the Order had been hording for so long… If only you had time to fully study it...

Despite facing your foe on a graveyard, supposedly the natural habitat for any necromancer, you are unable to gain any advantage over him. The ground here is consecrated, and the buried that were not worthy of being raised against you lie peacefully beneath holy earth. You need to penetrate this blasted protection if you want to get at the abundant parts right beneath your feet. The question is, how?

The Cathedral is the heart of the Order’s power. From here the Grand Magister commands his fanatical forces and enjoys total dominion over the surrounding lands. Usually one might only hear whispers in the hallowed corridors but now they are filled with the sounds of blades being drawn and armored boots hitting stone. Dim moonlight pours in through the high windows as an unearthly battlecry bellows forth from the decaying throats of your minions.

Buried just beneath the surface are the Catacombs, the dark secret of the Order. Here they train mages so that they can conduct sinister and dangerous experiments. It was always meant to stay a secret but recent necromancer troubles have let the knowledge of this place to slip into the public.
